Docs.remarks:
The  of an assembly differs from the  in that the CodeBase is the original location of the assembly, while the Location tells the location of the loaded assembly. These paths will differ if, for example, the assembly was shadow copied before loading.



This example demonstrates the use of the CodeBase Property

using System;
using System.Reflection;

class ReflectionTest
{
	public static void Main(string[] args){
		Assembly a = Assembly.GetAssembly(typeof(string));
		Console.WriteLine("CodeBase: {0}\n",a.CodeBase);
	}
}


Prints


CodeBase: file:///usr/local/lib/mono/1.0/mscorlib.dll

